  "texts": [
    "• Lastly, CCAM-Person incorporates the concept of Coordinate Attention (CA) 25 and designs a novel Context Coordinate Attention Module (CCAM) to enhance the precision of pose estimation through addressing issues caused by environmental noise or occluded body parts.",
    "Currently, mainstream strategies for MPE can be classified into two categories: single-stage and two-stage, as shown in Fig. 2.",
    "The two-stage approach initially employs object detectors or pedestrian detectors to detect human instances in the image.",
    "Then, for each detected human instance, a single-person pose estimation model is utilized for pose estimation.",
    "On the other hand, the single-stage approach identifies and connects the keypoints of human bodies through keypoint detection and association analysis."
  ],
